[[File:Cloughmore Stone, Rostrevor, July 2010 (04).JPG|thumb|300px|The view towards Carlingford Lough]]
'''Cloughmore''' or '''Cloghmore''' ({{etymology|ga|An Chloch Mhór|the big stone}}),<ref>{{cite web|title=Cloghmore|work=Place Names NI|url=http://www.placenamesni.org/resultdetails.php?entry=15103|accessdate=31 May 2018}}</ref> known locally as "The Big Stone", is a huge granite boulder perched on a mountainside almost {{convert|1000|ft|m}} above the village of [[Rostrevor]], [[County Down]], [[Northern Ireland]].<ref name="MVC">{{cite web|title=Cloughmore (Big Stone)|work=Cloughmore Male Voice Choir|url=http://www.cloughmoremvc.co.uk/cloughmore.htm|accessdate=2008-06-08|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080229074248/http://www.cloughmoremvc.co.uk/cloughmore.htm|archivedate=2008-02-29}}</ref> It sits on the slopes of Slieve Martin, overlooking Rostrevor Forest, [[Carlingford Lough]] and the [[Cooley Peninsula]]. It is popular destination for visitors, and is part of a National Nature Reserve and Area of Special Scientific Interest.<ref>[http://www.walkni.com/walks/259/rostrevor-cloughmore-stone/ Rostrevor - Cloughmore Stone]. Walk NI. Retrieved 31 May 2018.</ref>

The granite boulder, which has a calculated mass of 50 tonnes,<ref>{{cite web|title=Mourne Cooley Gullion geotourism 3D|url=https://sketchfab.com/models/9a74494d93024599ae1655d908f34c03|accessdate=18 May 2015}}</ref> is a [[glacial erratic]], thought to have been transported from [[Scotland]] (from an island in [[Strathclyde]] bay)<ref>{{cite web|title=Drumlin Country|work=The Newry Journal|date=22 April 2004|url=http://www.newryjournal.co.uk/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=386&Itemid=31|accessdate=2008-06-08}}</ref> and deposited about 10,000 years ago by retreating ice during the [[Last glacial period|last Ice Age]].<ref name="MVC"/> It sits on a relatively flat area of Silurian metasedimentary rock.

Local legend has it that the stone was thrown from the [[Cooley Mountains]], on the other side of Carlingford Lough, by the giant [[Fionn mac Cumhaill]].<ref name="MVC"/>

